			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">The only issue I see with Alphabetical tracking is this:
<br />

<br />
What possible in-game explanation is there for that ability?
<br />

<br />
I can understand the stuff about sorting by distance, and even the newest spawns (freshest tracks) but what possible clues could your Ranger pick up that would differentiate between mobs whose name begins with "B" and thos whose name begins with "S"? He'd have to work out what the mob was, then do it in his head, which, for me, translates as searching through the Track List. 
<br />

<br />
Which, believe me, I'd love to do.
<br />

<br />
LDoN.
<br />

<br />
"Surge, any Named up?"
<br />
....
<br />
....
<br />
"Hang on guys, I can track the entire dungeon and they're all blue. This may take some time..."
<br />
SCRROOOOOLLLLLLLLLLLL.........
<br />

<br />
It'd be nice to be able to sort all the mobs called "a ..." to the bottom
<br />

<br />
I just can't see any in-game justification for it.<br />_________________<br /><image src="http://www.toogeektolive.org.uk/images/surgecrit.jpg"><BR>
<br />
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=660181" target="_blank" class="postlink">Surgen Sureglade - 55 Outrider of Tunare</a><BR>Vazaelle Server</span><span class="gentblsmall"></span></td>
