<br />

<br />
Which, to me, is a different fettle of kish entirely.
<br />

<br />
If I'm in a zone, looking for The Abominable Snowman, currently I track all the mobs in zone, find his prints, click on his name in the list (after mucho scrollness) and off I go, tracking to him and him only.
<br />

<br />
What you're talking about, I think, is the ability to open up track, type in "Abominable Snowman" as a search term (or "The Abominable" if you prefer) and it lists only mobs matching those terms. A Searchable listing would be better (and really nice) and I can see some justification for this, as you say.
<br />

<br />
I still can't see how you'd blag the ability to list all mobs in track range alphabetically, as an innate ability. Perhaps as an AA "Brain Wired for Tracking - He's a complete freak" it might be do-able but not as a general Track ability. And even then I still don't like it much, it smacks of "We couldn't really justify this one, so we made it an AA, called it 'special' and hoped that'd do".
<br />

<br />
Maybe it's just me, though  <img src="images/smiles/icon_wink.gif" alt="icon_wink.gif" border="0" /><br />_________________<br /><image src="http://www.toogeektolive.org.uk/images/surgecrit.jpg"><BR>
